            "sections": [
              {
                "heading": "1. What is Homeostasis?",
                "content": "**Homeostasis** = the maintenance of stable internal conditions despite changes in the external environment.\n\n**Key Idea:** Your body has a 'set point' for many variables:\n- Body temperature: ~37¬∞C\n- Blood glucose: 4-6 mmol/L\n- Blood pH: 7.35-7.45\n- Water balance: precise fluid levels\n\nWhen conditions drift from the set point, the body responds to bring them back.\n\n**Why it matters:** Cells need stable conditions to function. Too hot, too cold, too acidic, too much sugar ‚Äî all of these can damage cells or stop chemical reactions from working properly.",
                "keyTerm": {
                  "term": "Homeostasis",
                  "definition": "The maintenance of a stable internal environment despite external changes",
                  "example": "Body temperature staying at 37¬∞C whether you're in a snowstorm or a desert"
