                "heading": "5. What Happens When Homeostasis Fails?",
                "content": "**Hypothermia** (body temp < 35¬∞C)\n- Feedback systems can't generate enough heat\n- Cells slow down, organs fail, risk of death\n\n**Hyperthermia/Heat Stroke** (body temp > 40¬∞C)\n- Cooling systems overwhelmed\n- Proteins denature, brain damage risk\n\n**Diabetes** (blood sugar regulation fails)\n- Type 1: Pancreas doesn't make insulin\n- Type 2: Cells stop responding to insulin\n- Result: Blood sugar stays dangerously high\n\n**Dehydration**\n- Water balance disrupted\n- Blood thickens, organs can't function, heatstroke risk increases",
